radiographic_examinations.findings: Fatty infiltrated liver with area of sparing in the right lobe, mild fat stranding surrounding the appendix, mildly thickened and dilated appendix measuring up to 8 mm, concerning for appendicitis, colonic diverticulosis with no evidence of acute diverticulitis, small fat-containing umbilical hernia, mildly hyperdense material in the gallbladder possibly representing small gallstones, calcified structure in the mid lower abdomen, left ovary with multiple small cysts, unremarkable osseous structures, focal area of hypodensity in the L4 vertebral body.
